            "type": "IntroCard", 
            "id": "intro_card_0"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "Layers help the two-dimensional space of a photo better represent the three-dimensional world. This lesson will teach you the basic steps to create photos with layers.", 
            "type": "BasicTextCard", 
            "id": "text_card_0"
        }, 
        {
            "header": "Next", 
            "text": "Start", 
            "type": "ButtonCard", 
            "id": "milestone_start", 
            "icon": "down"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "The most basic way to use layers is with two distinct layers: a subject layer and a context layer. The context layer provides additional information related to your subject.", 
            "type": "BasicTextCard", 
            "id": "text_card_1", 
            "references": [
                "create_layers::milestone_start::value::true"
            ]
        }, 
        {
            "medium": "photo", 
            "media": [
                {
                    "media": "2.jpg", 
                    "media_caption": null
                }
            ], 
            "header": "In this photo the subject layer is in color.", 
            "references": [
                "create_layers::milestone_start::value::true"
            ], 
            "exampleMediaPath": "2.jpg", 
            "clipType": "character", 
            "type": "ExampleCard", 
            "id": "preview_card_0"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "The subject layer shows the main subject of your photo. This is usually a person or an object. The subject layer is often placed in the foreground layer of your frame.", 
            "type": "BasicTextCard", 
            "id": "text_card_2", 
            "references": [
                "create_layers::milestone_start::value::true"
            ]
        }, 
        {
            "medium": "photo", 
            "media": [
                {
                    "media": "3.jpg", 
                    "media_caption": null
                }
            ], 
            "header": "In this photo the context layer is in color.", 
            "references": [
                "create_layers::milestone_start::value::true"
            ], 
            "exampleMediaPath": "3.jpg", 
            "clipType": "character", 
            "type": "ExampleCard", 
            "id": "preview_card_1"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "The context layer is often the background layer. It helps the viewer better understand a subject's environment or an important detail of the story. In this photo the context layer tells the viewer the women are at a protest.", 
            "type": "BasicTextCard", 
            "id": "text_card_3", 
            "references": [
                "create_layers::milestone_start::value::true"
            ]
        }, 
        {
            "medium": "photo", 
            "media": [
                {
                    "media": "4.jpg", 
                    "media_caption": null
                }
            ], 
            "header": "Sometimes the layers are reversed, here the context layer is in the foreground.", 
            "references": [
                "create_layers::milestone_start::value::true"
            ], 
            "exampleMediaPath": "4.jpg", 
            "clipType": "character", 
            "type": "ExampleCard", 
            "id": "preview_card_2"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "This image highlights the context of the story \u2014 the game \u2014 by placing it in the foreground and placing the subject in the background.", 
            "type": "BasicTextCard", 
            "id": "text_card_4", 
